    public class MORDefinitionObjectProperty
extends MORObjectPropertyBase
implements MORObjectProperty.Disjoint<MORDefinitionObjectProperty>, MORObjectProperty.Equivalent<MORDefinitionObjectProperty>, MORObjectProperty.Inverse<MORDefinitionObjectProperty>
    A basic implementation for an object property with equivalent, disjoint and inverse properties.

    This is an example of how use the Descriptors for implement an object property that is synchronised w.r.t. its Disjoint, Equivalent and Inverse properties.
    Its purpose is only to instanciate the MORAxioms.ObjectLinks for the respective descriptions, as well as call both interfaces in the readSemantic() and writeSemantic() methods. All its constructions are based on MORObjectPropertyBase in order to automatically manage an ObjectInstance ground.
    You may want to use this class (see also MORDefinitionObjectProperty and MORHierarchicalObjectProperty,as well as other classes in the it.emarolab.owloop.aMORDescriptor.utility package) as templates to build a specific MORObjectProperty descriptor that fits your needs and maximises the OWL synchronisation efficiency for object properties.

      • readSemantic

        public java.util.List<Semantic.MappingIntent> readSemantic()
        Description copied from interface: Semantic.Descriptor
        This method is used to synchronise specific Semantic.Axioms (or Semantic.SemanticAxioms) from the ontology. It manipulates the OWLLOOP representation to be equal to the queried OWL structure. It is based on Axioms#synchroniseFrom(Axioms).
